    "lyrics": {
      "text": "To thee, the Cham---pion Lead-er, we thy flock now ded-i--cate a ho-ly feast___ of great thanks-giv-ing and of vic-to--ry, as ones res-cued out of suf-f’rings, O The-o-to-kos. But as thou___ art one with might which is in-vin-ci--ble, from all dan-gers that can be do thou de-liv-er us, that we may cry to__ thee: Re-joice, thou pure__ and un-wed--ded__ Bride. \n\nRe-joice, thou pure__ and un-wed-ded Bride.____"
    }
  }
